quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  18,103,"Say, [O Muḥammad], "
  18,104,"[They are] those whose effort is lost in worldly life, while they think that they are doing well in work."
  18,105,"Those are the ones who disbelieve in the verses of their Lord and in [their] meeting Him, so their deeds have become worthless; and We will not assign to them on the Day of Resurrection any weight [i.e., importance]."
  19,64,"[Gabriel said],{1} ",1:[In answer to the Prophet's wish that Gabriel would visit him more often.]
  19,65,"Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them - so worship Him and have patience for His worship. Do you know of any similarity to Him?"
  19,66,"And man [i.e., the disbeliever] says, "
  20,46,"[Allāh] said, "
  20,47,"So go to him and say, 'Indeed, we are messengers of your Lord, so send with us the Children of Israel and do not torment them. We have come to you with a sign from your Lord. And peace{1} will be upon he who follows the guidance.",1:[i.e., safety and security from Allāh's punishment.]
  20,48,"Indeed, it has been revealed to us that the punishment will be upon whoever denies and turns away.'"
  21,22,"Had there been within them [i.e., the heavens and earth] gods besides Allāh, they both would have been ruined. So exalted is Allāh, Lord of the Throne, above what they describe."
  21,23,"He is not questioned about what He does, but they will be questioned."
  21,24,"Or have they taken gods besides Him? Say, [O Muḥammad], ",1:[All previous prophets called for the worship of Allāh alone.]
